==English==

===Adjective===
'''clownish'''

# Of or pertaining to the actions a [[clown]], often in terms of [[inappropriate]] or [[boorish]] behaviour.
#:'''1815''' ''"He is very plain, undoubtedly--remarkably plain:--but that is nothing compared with his entire want of gentility. I had no right to expect much, and I did not expect much; but I had no idea that he could be so very '''clownish''', so totally without air. I had imagined him, I confess, a degree or two nearer gentility."'' — Jane Austen, ''Emma'', [[s:Emma/Volume 1/Chapter 4|Volume I, Chapter 4]].

